messages.message:
Patch Set 3:

Sorry, it's definitely the client default...

The server default is still either:
#if defined(LDISKFS_CLUSTER_SIZE)
        if (LDISKFS_CLUSTER_SIZE(sb) > DT_DEF_BRW_SIZE)
                param->ddp_brw_size = LDISKFS_CLUSTER_SIZE(sb);
        else
#endif
                param->ddp_brw_size = DT_DEF_BRW_SIZE;

Or, for ZFS, it's 1 MiB or block size, whichever is greater:
        if (osd->od_max_blksz > ONE_MB_BRW_SIZE)
                param->ddp_brw_size = osd->od_max_blksz;
        else
                param->ddp_brw_size = ONE_MB_BRW_SIZE;

I don't have a good sense of what typical values for block size and cluster bits are on ldiskfs, so I guess I don't know what typical real world ldiskfs default brw_size is...?  It's 4 on my test-framework set up VM, but that may not be representative.
